nt%20Analysis.%5Cn%5CnA%20classifier%20with%20a%20linear%20decision%20boundary%2C%20generated%20by%20fitting%20class%5Cnconditional%20densities%20to%20the%20data%20and%20using%20Bayes&#39;%20rule.%5Cn%5CnThe%20model%20fits%20a%20Gaussian%20density%20to%20each%20class%2C%20assuming%20that%20all%20classes%5Cnshare%20the%20same%20covariance%20matrix.%5Cn%5CnThe%20fitted%20model%20can%20also%20be%20used%20to%20reduce%20the%20dimensionality%20of%20the%20input%5Cnby%20projecting%20it%20to%20the%20most%20discriminative%20directions%2C%20using%20the%5Cn%60transform%60%20method.%5Cn%5CnFor%20a%20comparison%20between%20%20%5Cn%60~sklearn.discriminant_analysis.LinearDiscriminantAnalysis%60%20%20%5Cnand%20%60~sklearn.discriminant_analysis.QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis%60%2C%20see%20%20%5Cn%60sphx_glr_auto_examples_classification_plot_lda_qda.py%60.%5Cn%5CnRead%20more%20in%20the%20%60User%20Guide%20%3Clda_qda%3E%60.%5Cn%5CnParameters%5Cn----------%5Cnsolver%20%3A%20%7B&#39;svd&#39;%2C%20&#39;lsqr&#39;%2C%20&#39;eigen&#39;%7D%2C%20default%3D&#39;svd&#39;%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BSolver%20to%20use%2C%20possible%20values%3A%5Cn%20%20%20-%20&#39;svd&#39;%3A%20Singular%20value%20decomposition%20(default).%5CnDoes%20not%20compute%20the%20covariance%20matrix%2C%20therefore%20this%20solver%20is%5Cnrecommended%20for%20data%20with%20a%20large%20number%20of%20features.%5Cn%20%20%20-%20&#39;lsqr&#39;%3A%20Least%20squares%20solution.%5CnCan%20be%20combined%20with%20shrinkage%20or%20custom%20covariance%20estimator.%5Cn%20%20%20-%20&#39;eigen&#39;%3A%20Eigenvalue%20decomposition.%5CnCan%20be%20combined%20with%20shrinkage%20or%20custom%20covariance%20estimator.%5Cn%5Cnshrinkage%20%3A%20&#39;auto&#39;%20or%20float%2C%20default%3DNone%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BShrinkage%20parameter%2C%20possible%20values%3A%5Cn%20%20%20-%20None%3A%20no%20shrinkage%20(default).%5Cn%20%20%20-%20&#39;auto&#39;%3A%20automatic%20shrinkage%20using%20the%20Ledoit-Wolf%20lemma.%5Cn%20%20%20-%20float%20between%200%20and%201%3A%20fixed%20shrinkage%20parameter.%5Cn%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BThis%20should%20be%20left%20to%20None%20if%20%60covariance_estimator%60%20is%20used.%5CnNote%20that%20shrinkage%20works%20only%20with%20&#39;lsqr&#39;%20and%20&#39;eigen&#39;%20solvers.%5Cn%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BFor%20a%20usage%20example%2C%20see%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%60sphx_glr_auto_examples_classification_plot_lda.py%60.%5Cn%5Cnpriors%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C)%2C%20default%3DNone%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BThe%20class%20prior%20probabilities.%20By%20default%2C%20the%20class%20proportions%20are%5Cninferred%20from%20the%20training%20data.%5Cn%5Cnn%5C%5C_components%20%3A%20int%2C%20default%3DNone%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BNumber%20of%20components%20(%26lt%3B%3D%20min(n%5C%5C_classes%20-%201%2C%20n%5C%5C_features))%20for%5Cndimensionality%20reduction.%20If%20None%2C%20will%20be%20set%20to%5Cnmin(n%5C%5C_classes%20-%201%2C%20n%5C%5C_features).%20This%20parameter%20only%20affects%20the%5Cn%60transform%60%20method.%5Cn%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BFor%20a%20usage%20example%2C%20see%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%60sphx_glr_auto_examples_decomposition_plot_pca_vs_lda.py%60.%5Cn%5Cnstore%5C%5C_covariance%20%3A%20bool%2C%20default%3DFalse%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BIf%20True%2C%20explicitly%20compute%20the%20weighted%20within-class%20covariance%5Cnmatrix%20when%20solver%20is%20&#39;svd&#39;.%20The%20matrix%20is%20always%20computed%5Cnand%20stored%20for%20the%20other%20solvers.%5Cn%5Cntol%20%3A%20float%2C%20default%3D1.0e-4%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BAbsolute%20threshold%20for%20a%20singular%20value%20of%20X%20to%20be%20considered%5Cnsignificant%2C%20used%20to%20estimate%20the%20rank%20of%20X.%20Dimensions%20whose%5Cnsingular%20values%20are%20non-significant%20are%20discarded.%20Only%20used%20if%5Cnsolver%20is%20&#39;svd&#39;.%5Cn%5Cncovariance%5C%5C_estimator%20%3A%20covariance%20estimator%2C%20default%3DNone%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BIf%20not%20None%2C%20%60covariance_estimator%60%20is%20used%20to%20estimate%5Cnthe%20covariance%20matrices%20instead%20of%20relying%20on%20the%20empirical%5Cncovariance%20estimator%20(with%20potential%20shrinkage).%5CnThe%20object%20should%20have%20a%20fit%20method%20and%20a%20%60covariance_%60%20attribute%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3Blike%20the%20estimators%20in%20%60sklearn.covariance%60.%5Cnif%20None%20the%20shrinkage%20parameter%20drives%20the%20estimate.%5Cn%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BThis%20should%20be%20left%20to%20None%20if%20%60shrinkage%60%20is%20used.%5CnNote%20that%20%60covariance_estimator%60%20works%20only%20with%20&#39;lsqr&#39;%20and%20&#39;eigen&#39;%5Cnsolvers.%5Cn%5CnAttributes%5Cn----------%5Cncoef%5C%5C_%20%3A%20ndarray%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_features%2C)%20or%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C%20n%5C%5C_features)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BWeight%20vector(s).%5Cn%5Cnintercept%5C%5C_%20%3A%20ndarray%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BIntercept%20term.%5Cn%5Cncovariance%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_features%2C%20n%5C%5C_features)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BWeighted%20within-class%20covariance%20matrix.%20It%20corresponds%20to%5Cn%60sum_k%20prior_k%20*%20C_k%60%20where%20%60C_k%60%20is%20the%20covariance%20matrix%20of%20the%5Cnsamples%20in%20class%20%60k%60.%20The%20%60C_k%60%20are%20estimated%20using%20the%20(potentially%5Cnshrunk)%20biased%20estimator%20of%20covariance.%20If%20solver%20is%20&#39;svd&#39;%2C%20only%5Cnexists%20when%20%60store_covariance%60%20is%20True.%5Cn%5Cnexplained%5C%5C_variance%5C%5C_ratio%5C%5C_%20%3A%20ndarray%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_components%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BPercentage%20of%20variance%20explained%20by%20each%20of%20the%20selected%20components.%5CnIf%20%60n_components%60%20is%20not%20set%20then%20all%20components%20are%20stored%20and%20the%5Cnsum%20of%20explained%20variances%20is%20equal%20to%201.0.%20Only%20available%20when%20eigen%5Cnor%20svd%20solver%20is%20used.%5Cn%5Cnmeans%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C%20n%5C%5C_features)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BClass-wise%20means.%5Cn%5Cnpriors%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BClass%20priors%20(sum%20to%201).%5Cn%5Cnscalings%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(rank%2C%20n%5C%5C_classes%20-%201)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BScaling%20of%20the%20features%20in%20the%20space%20spanned%20by%20the%20class%20centroids.%5CnOnly%20available%20for%20&#39;svd&#39;%20and%20&#39;eigen&#39;%20solvers.%5Cn%5Cnxbar%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_features%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BOverall%20mean.%20Only%20present%20if%20solver%20is%20&#39;svd&#39;.%5Cn%5Cnclasses%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BUnique%20class%20labels.%5Cn%5Cnn%5C%5C_features%5C%5C_in%5C%5C_%20%3A%20int%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BNumber%20of%20features%20seen%20during%20%60fit%60.%5Cn%5Cnfeature%5C%5C_names%5C%5C_in%5C%5C_%20%3A%20ndarray%20of%20shape%20(%60n_features_in_%60%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BNames%20of%20features%20seen%20during%20%60fit%60.%20Defined%20only%20when%20%60X%60%5Cnhas%20feature%20names%20that%20are%20all%20strings.%5Cn%5CnSee%20Also%5Cn--------%5CnQuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis%20%3A%20Quadratic%20Discriminant%20Analysis.%5Cn%5CnExamples%5Cn--------%5Cn%60%60%60%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20import%20numpy%20as%20np%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20from%20sklearn.discriminant_analysis%20import%20LinearDiscriminantAnalysis%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20X%20%3D%20np.array(%5B%5B-1%2C%20-1%5D%2C%20%5B-2%2C%20-1%5D%2C%20%5B-3%2C%20-2%5D%2C%20%5B1%2C%201%5D%2C%20%5B2%2C%201%5D%2C%20%5B3%2C%202%5D%5D)%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20y%20%3D%20np.array(%5B1%2C%201%2C%201%2C%202%2C%202%2C%202%5D)%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20clf%20%3D%20LinearDiscriminantAnalysis()%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20clf.fit(X%2C%20y)%5CnLinearDiscriminantAnalysis()%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20print(clf.predict(%5B%5B-0.8%2C%20-1%5D%5D))%5Cn%5B1%5D%5Cn%60%60%60%22%5D" href="https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1GLzxxkbqDWVwybZGUKTe1Gvv8f4wlDZ9" title="command:pinDocumentation?%5B%22LinearDiscriminantAnalysis%22%2C%22%60%60%60python%5Cndef%20__init__(solver%3D&#39;svd&#39;%2C%20shrinkage%3DNone%2C%20priors%3DNone%2C%20n_components%3DNone%2C%20store_covariance%3DFalse%2C%20tol%3D0.0001%2C%20covariance_estimator%3DNone)%5Cn%60%60%60%5Cn%5CnLinear%20Discriminant%20Analysis.%5Cn%5CnA%20classifier%20with%20a%20linear%20decision%20boundary%2C%20generated%20by%20fitting%20class%5Cnconditional%20densities%20to%20the%20data%20and%20using%20Bayes&#39;%20rule.%5Cn%5CnThe%20model%20fits%20a%20Gaussian%20density%20to%20each%20class%2C%20assuming%20that%20all%20classes%5Cnshare%20the%20same%20covariance%20matrix.%5Cn%5CnThe%20fitted%20model%20can%20also%20be%20used%20to%20reduce%20the%20dimensionality%20of%20the%20input%5Cnby%20projecting%20it%20to%20the%20most%20discriminative%20directions%2C%20using%20the%5Cn%60transform%60%20method.%5Cn%5CnFor%20a%20comparison%20between%20%20%5Cn%60~sklearn.discriminant_analysis.LinearDiscriminantAnalysis%60%20%20%5Cnand%20%60~sklearn.discriminant_analysis.QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis%60%2C%20see%20%20%5Cn%60sphx_glr_auto_examples_classification_plot_lda_qda.py%60.%5Cn%5CnRead%20more%20in%20the%20%60User%20Guide%20%3Clda_qda%3E%60.%5Cn%5CnParameters%5Cn----------%5Cnsolver%20%3A%20%7B&#39;svd&#39;%2C%20&#39;lsqr&#39;%2C%20&#39;eigen&#39;%7D%2C%20default%3D&#39;svd&#39;%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BSolver%20to%20use%2C%20possible%20values%3A%5Cn%20%20%20-%20&#39;svd&#39;%3A%20Singular%20value%20decomposition%20(default).%5CnDoes%20not%20compute%20the%20covariance%20matrix%2C%20therefore%20this%20solver%20is%5Cnrecommended%20for%20data%20with%20a%20large%20number%20of%20features.%5Cn%20%20%20-%20&#39;lsqr&#39;%3A%20Least%20squares%20solution.%5CnCan%20be%20combined%20with%20shrinkage%20or%20custom%20covariance%20estimator.%5Cn%20%20%20-%20&#39;eigen&#39;%3A%20Eigenvalue%20decomposition.%5CnCan%20be%20combined%20with%20shrinkage%20or%20custom%20covariance%20estimator.%5Cn%5Cnshrinkage%20%3A%20&#39;auto&#39;%20or%20float%2C%20default%3DNone%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BShrinkage%20parameter%2C%20possible%20values%3A%5Cn%20%20%20-%20None%3A%20no%20shrinkage%20(default).%5Cn%20%20%20-%20&#39;auto&#39;%3A%20automatic%20shrinkage%20using%20the%20Ledoit-Wolf%20lemma.%5Cn%20%20%20-%20float%20between%200%20and%201%3A%20fixed%20shrinkage%20parameter.%5Cn%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BThis%20should%20be%20left%20to%20None%20if%20%60covariance_estimator%60%20is%20used.%5CnNote%20that%20shrinkage%20works%20only%20with%20&#39;lsqr&#39;%20and%20&#39;eigen&#39;%20solvers.%5Cn%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BFor%20a%20usage%20example%2C%20see%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%60sphx_glr_auto_examples_classification_plot_lda.py%60.%5Cn%5Cnpriors%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C)%2C%20default%3DNone%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BThe%20class%20prior%20probabilities.%20By%20default%2C%20the%20class%20proportions%20are%5Cninferred%20from%20the%20training%20data.%5Cn%5Cnn%5C%5C_components%20%3A%20int%2C%20default%3DNone%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BNumber%20of%20components%20(%26lt%3B%3D%20min(n%5C%5C_classes%20-%201%2C%20n%5C%5C_features))%20for%5Cndimensionality%20reduction.%20If%20None%2C%20will%20be%20set%20to%5Cnmin(n%5C%5C_classes%20-%201%2C%20n%5C%5C_features).%20This%20parameter%20only%20affects%20the%5Cn%60transform%60%20method.%5Cn%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BFor%20a%20usage%20example%2C%20see%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%60sphx_glr_auto_examples_decomposition_plot_pca_vs_lda.py%60.%5Cn%5Cnstore%5C%5C_covariance%20%3A%20bool%2C%20default%3DFalse%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BIf%20True%2C%20explicitly%20compute%20the%20weighted%20within-class%20covariance%5Cnmatrix%20when%20solver%20is%20&#39;svd&#39;.%20The%20matrix%20is%20always%20computed%5Cnand%20stored%20for%20the%20other%20solvers.%5Cn%5Cntol%20%3A%20float%2C%20default%3D1.0e-4%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BAbsolute%20threshold%20for%20a%20singular%20value%20of%20X%20to%20be%20considered%5Cnsignificant%2C%20used%20to%20estimate%20the%20rank%20of%20X.%20Dimensions%20whose%5Cnsingular%20values%20are%20non-significant%20are%20discarded.%20Only%20used%20if%5Cnsolver%20is%20&#39;svd&#39;.%5Cn%5Cncovariance%5C%5C_estimator%20%3A%20covariance%20estimator%2C%20default%3DNone%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BIf%20not%20None%2C%20%60covariance_estimator%60%20is%20used%20to%20estimate%5Cnthe%20covariance%20matrices%20instead%20of%20relying%20on%20the%20empirical%5Cncovariance%20estimator%20(with%20potential%20shrinkage).%5CnThe%20object%20should%20have%20a%20fit%20method%20and%20a%20%60covariance_%60%20attribute%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3Blike%20the%20estimators%20in%20%60sklearn.covariance%60.%5Cnif%20None%20the%20shrinkage%20parameter%20drives%20the%20estimate.%5Cn%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BThis%20should%20be%20left%20to%20None%20if%20%60shrinkage%60%20is%20used.%5CnNote%20that%20%60covariance_estimator%60%20works%20only%20with%20&#39;lsqr&#39;%20and%20&#39;eigen&#39;%5Cnsolvers.%5Cn%5CnAttributes%5Cn----------%5Cncoef%5C%5C_%20%3A%20ndarray%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_features%2C)%20or%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C%20n%5C%5C_features)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BWeight%20vector(s).%5Cn%5Cnintercept%5C%5C_%20%3A%20ndarray%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BIntercept%20term.%5Cn%5Cncovariance%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_features%2C%20n%5C%5C_features)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BWeighted%20within-class%20covariance%20matrix.%20It%20corresponds%20to%5Cn%60sum_k%20prior_k%20*%20C_k%60%20where%20%60C_k%60%20is%20the%20covariance%20matrix%20of%20the%5Cnsamples%20in%20class%20%60k%60.%20The%20%60C_k%60%20are%20estimated%20using%20the%20(potentially%5Cnshrunk)%20biased%20estimator%20of%20covariance.%20If%20solver%20is%20&#39;svd&#39;%2C%20only%5Cnexists%20when%20%60store_covariance%60%20is%20True.%5Cn%5Cnexplained%5C%5C_variance%5C%5C_ratio%5C%5C_%20%3A%20ndarray%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_components%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BPercentage%20of%20variance%20explained%20by%20each%20of%20the%20selected%20components.%5CnIf%20%60n_components%60%20is%20not%20set%20then%20all%20components%20are%20stored%20and%20the%5Cnsum%20of%20explained%20variances%20is%20equal%20to%201.0.%20Only%20available%20when%20eigen%5Cnor%20svd%20solver%20is%20used.%5Cn%5Cnmeans%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C%20n%5C%5C_features)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BClass-wise%20means.%5Cn%5Cnpriors%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BClass%20priors%20(sum%20to%201).%5Cn%5Cnscalings%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(rank%2C%20n%5C%5C_classes%20-%201)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BScaling%20of%20the%20features%20in%20the%20space%20spanned%20by%20the%20class%20centroids.%5CnOnly%20available%20for%20&#39;svd&#39;%20and%20&#39;eigen&#39;%20solvers.%5Cn%5Cnxbar%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_features%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BOverall%20mean.%20Only%20present%20if%20solver%20is%20&#39;svd&#39;.%5Cn%5Cnclasses%5C%5C_%20%3A%20array-like%20of%20shape%20(n%5C%5C_classes%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BUnique%20class%20labels.%5Cn%5Cnn%5C%5C_features%5C%5C_in%5C%5C_%20%3A%20int%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BNumber%20of%20features%20seen%20during%20%60fit%60.%5Cn%5Cnfeature%5C%5C_names%5C%5C_in%5C%5C_%20%3A%20ndarray%20of%20shape%20(%60n_features_in_%60%2C)%20%20%5Cn%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3BNames%20of%20features%20seen%20during%20%60fit%60.%20Defined%20only%20when%20%60X%60%5Cnhas%20feature%20names%20that%20are%20all%20strings.%5Cn%5CnSee%20Also%5Cn--------%5CnQuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis%20%3A%20Quadratic%20Discriminant%20Analysis.%5Cn%5CnExamples%5Cn--------%5Cn%60%60%60%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20import%20numpy%20as%20np%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20from%20sklearn.discriminant_analysis%20import%20LinearDiscriminantAnalysis%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20X%20%3D%20np.array(%5B%5B-1%2C%20-1%5D%2C%20%5B-2%2C%20-1%5D%2C%20%5B-3%2C%20-2%5D%2C%20%5B1%2C%201%5D%2C%20%5B2%2C%201%5D%2C%20%5B3%2C%202%5D%5D)%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20y%20%3D%20np.array(%5B1%2C%201%2C%201%2C%202%2C%202%2C%202%5D)%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20clf%20%3D%20LinearDiscriminantAnalysis()%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20clf.fit(X%2C%20y)%5CnLinearDiscriminantAnalysis()%5Cn%3E%3E%3E%20print(clf.predict(%5B%5B-0.8%2C%20-1%5D%5D))%5Cn%5B1%5D%5Cn%60%60%60%22%5D" draggable="false">Open in tab</a>     <a data-href="command:viewSource?%5B%22file%3A%2F%2F%2Fusr%2Flocal%2Flib%2Fpython3.12%2Fdist-packages%2Fsklearn%2Fdiscriminant_analysis.py%22%2C%7B%22startLineNumber%22%3A249%2C%22startColumn%22%3A1%2C%22endLineNumber%22%3A249%2C%22endColumn%22%3A1%7D%5D" href="https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1GLzxxkbqDWVwybZGUKTe1Gvv8f4wlDZ9" title="command:viewSource?%5B%22file%3A%2F%2F%2Fusr%2Flocal%2Flib%2Fpython3.12%2Fdist-packages%2Fsklearn%2Fdiscriminant_analysis.py%22%2C%7B%22startLineNumber%22%3A249%2C%22startColumn%22%3A1%2C%22endLineNumber%22%3A249%2C%22endColumn%22%3A1%7D%5D" draggable="false">View source</a></p></div></div></div><div class="markdown-hover"><div class="hover-contents code-hover-contents"><div class="rendered-markdown"><p>Linear Discriminant Analysis.</p><p>A classifier with a linear decision boundary, generated by fitting class
conditional densities to the data and using Bayes' rule.</p><p>The model fits a Gaussian density to each class, assuming that all classes
share the same covariance matrix.</p><p>The fitted model can also be used to reduce the dimensionality of the input
by projecting it to the most discriminative directions, using the
<code>transform</code> method.</p><p>For a comparison between<br><code>~sklearn.discriminant_analysis.LinearDiscriminantAnalysis</code><br>and <code>~sklearn.discriminant_analysis.QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis</code>, see<br><code>sphx_glr_auto_examples_classification_plot_lda_qda.py</code>.</p><p>Read more in the <code>User Guide &lt;lda_qda&gt;</code>.</p><h2>Parameters</h2>
<p>solver : {'svd', 'lsqr', 'eigen'}, default='svd'<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Solver to use, possible values:</p><ul>
<li>'svd': Singular value decomposition (default).
Does not compute the covariance matrix, therefore this solver is
recommended for data with a large number of features.</li>
<li>'lsqr': Least squares solution.
Can be combined with shrinkage or custom covariance estimator.</li>
<li>'eigen': Eigenvalue decomposition.
Can be combined with shrinkage or custom covariance estimator.</li>
</ul>
<p>shrinkage : 'auto' or float, default=None<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Shrinkage parameter, possible values:</p><ul>
<li>None: no shrinkage (default).</li>
<li>'auto': automatic shrinkage using the Ledoit-Wolf lemma.</li>
<li>float between 0 and 1: fixed shrinkage parameter.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This should be left to None if <code>covariance_estimator</code> is used.
Note that shrinkage works only with 'lsqr' and 'eigen' solvers.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For a usage example, see<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<code>sphx_glr_auto_examples_classification_plot_lda.py</code>.</p><p>priors : array-like of shape (n_classes,), default=None<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The class prior probabilities. By default, the class proportions are
inferred from the training data.</p><p>n_components : int, default=None<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Number of components (&lt;= min(n_classes - 1, n_features)) for
dimensionality reduction. If None, will be set to
min(n_classes - 1, n_features). This parameter only affects the
<code>transform</code> method.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For a usage example, see<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<code>sphx_glr_auto_examples_decomposition_plot_pca_vs_lda.py</code>.</p><p>store_covariance : bool, default=False<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If True, explicitly compute the weighted within-class covariance
matrix when solver is 'svd'. The matrix is always computed
and stored for the other solvers.</p><p>tol : float, default=1.0e-4<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Absolute threshold for a singular value of X to be considered
significant, used to estimate the rank of X. Dimensions whose
singular values are non-significant are discarded. Only used if
solver is 'svd'.</p><p>covariance_estimator : covariance estimator, default=None<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If not None, <code>covariance_estimator</code> is used to estimate
the covariance matrices instead of relying on the empirical
covariance estimator (with potential shrinkage).
The object should have a fit method and a <code>covariance_</code> attribute<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;like the estimators in <code>sklearn.covariance</code>.
if None the shrinkage parameter drives the estimate.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This should be left to None if <code>shrinkage</code> is used.
Note that <code>covariance_estimator</code> works only with 'lsqr' and 'eigen'
solvers.</p><h2>Attributes</h2>
<p>coef_ : ndarray of shape (n_features,) or (n_classes, n_features)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Weight vector(s).</p><p>intercept_ : ndarray of shape (n_classes,)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Intercept term.</p><p>covariance_ : array-like of shape (n_features, n_features)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Weighted within-class covariance matrix. It corresponds to
<code>sum_k prior_k * C_k</code> where <code>C_k</code> is the covariance matrix of the
samples in class <code>k</code>. The <code>C_k</code> are estimated using the (potentially
shrunk) biased estimator of covariance. If solver is 'svd', only
exists when <code>store_covariance</code> is True.</p><p>explained_variance_ratio_ : ndarray of shape (n_components,)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Percentage of variance explained by each of the selected components.
If <code>n_components</code> is not set then all components are stored and the
sum of explained variances is equal to 1.0. Only available when eigen
or svd solver is used.</p><p>means_ : array-like of shape (n_classes, n_features)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Class-wise means.</p><p>priors_ : array-like of shape (n_classes,)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Class priors (sum to 1).</p><p>scalings_ : array-like of shape (rank, n_classes - 1)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scaling of the features in the space spanned by the class centroids.
Only available for 'svd' and 'eigen' solvers.</p><p>xbar_ : array-like of shape (n_features,)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Overall mean. Only present if solver is 'svd'.</p><p>classes_ : array-like of shape (n_classes,)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Unique class labels.</p><p>n_features_in_ : int<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Number of features seen during <code>fit</code>.</p><p>feature_names_in_ : ndarray of shape (<code>n_features_in_</code>,)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Names of features seen during <code>fit</code>. Defined only when <code>X</code>
has feature names that are all strings.</p><h2>See Also</h2>
<p>QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis : Quadratic Discriminant Analysis.</p><h2>Examples</h2>
<div data-code="id#6"><span style="font-family: monospace, Consolas, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0, &quot;calt&quot; 0; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 19px; letter-spacing: 0px;"><div class="monaco-tokenized-source"><span class="mtk1">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class="mtk20">import</span><span class="mtk1"> numpy </span><span class="mtk20">as</span><span class="mtk1"> np</span><br><span class="mtk1">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class="mtk20">from</span><span class="mtk1"> sklearn.discriminant_analysis </span><span class="mtk20">import</span><span class="mtk1"> LinearDiscriminantAnalysis</span><br><span class="mtk1">&gt;&gt;&gt; X = np.array</span><span class="mtk14">([[</span><span class="mtk6">-1</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">-1</span><span class="mtk14">],</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk14">[</span><span class="mtk6">-2</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">-1</span><span class="mtk14">],</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk14">[</span><span class="mtk6">-3</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">-2</span><span class="mtk14">],</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk14">[</span><span class="mtk6">1</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">1</span><span class="mtk14">],</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk14">[</span><span class="mtk6">2</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">1</span><span class="mtk14">],</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk14">[</span><span class="mtk6">3</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">2</span><span class="mtk14">]])</span><br><span class="mtk1">&gt;&gt;&gt; y = np.array</span><span class="mtk14">([</span><span class="mtk6">1</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">1</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">1</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">2</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">2</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">2</span><span class="mtk14">])</span><br><span class="mtk1">&gt;&gt;&gt; clf = LinearDiscriminantAnalysis</span><span class="mtk14">()</span><br><span class="mtk1">&gt;&gt;&gt; clf.fit</span><span class="mtk14">(</span><span class="mtk1">X</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> y</span><span class="mtk14">)</span><br><span class="mtk1">LinearDiscriminantAnalysis</span><span class="mtk14">()</span><br><span class="mtk1">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class="mtk17">print</span><span class="mtk14">(</span><span class="mtk1">clf.predict</span><span class="mtk14">([[</span><span class="mtk6">-0.8</span><span class="mtk14">,</span><span class="mtk1"> </span><span class="mtk6">-1</span><span class="mtk14">]]))</span><br><span class="mtk14">[</span><span class="mtk6">1</span><span class="mtk14">]</span></div></span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" class="invisible scrollbar horizontal" style="position: absolute;"><div class="slider" style="position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; height: 10px; transform: translate3d(0px, 0px, 0px); contain: strict;"></div></div><div role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" class="invisible scrollbar vertical" style="position: absolute;"><div class="slider" style="position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 10px; transform: translate3d(0px, 0px, 0px); contain: strict;"></div></div><div class="shadow"></div><div class="shadow"></div><div class="shadow"></div></div></div></div></div><div data-mprt="5" class="overflowingOverlayWidgets"></div><div class=".in-cell-overflowing"><div wid